12 An Act relating to schools; requiring district boards
of education to adopt a policy prohibiting student
13 cell phone and personal electronic device use under
certain circumstances; requiring exceptions for
14 emergencies; allowing board approval to opt out of
prohibition; requiring annual approval of alternative
15 policies; defining terms; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
16 emergency.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. Before the start of the 2025-2026 school year, each school
24 district board of education shall adopt a policy to prohibit the use
