1 of c ell phones and personal electronic devices by students enrolled
2 in the district during the entirety of the school day and while
3 present on school grounds.
4 B. District policies described in subsection A of this section
5 shall incorporate provisions for emergency use including, but not
6 limited to, use to support medical issues documented by a licensed
7 medical professional.
8 C. Notwithstanding subsection A of this section, a school
9 district board of education may vote to adopt a policy allowing
10 student cell phone or personal electronic device usage during the
11 school day. Any such policy shall be reviewed and approved by the
12 district board on an annual basis.
13 D. For purposes of this section:
14 1. "Cell phone" means a portable wireless telephone device that
15 is designed to send or receive transmissions through a cellular
16 radiotelephone service;
17 2. "Personal electronic device" means any personal device
18 capable of connecting to a smart phone, the Internet, a cellular or
19 Wi-Fi network, or directly connecting to another similar device.
20 Personal electronic devices include, but are not limited to, smart
21 watches, smart headphones, laptops, tablets, and smart glasses.
22 Personal electronic devices shall not include devices that are
23 school-issued or school-approved and specifically limited for use in
24 classroom instruction; and
